column5: Headed to Wawa for the weekend Through LSSP. Beauty day to travel. Sunny and cool  Lotsa snow      Like, lotsa snow. Got the Vector stuck 10 times, the Voyager almost the same      4 hours to get a couple km into camp 2 wore out dudes at the end of that day. We took the easy way out the next day. 30km to our second choice lake. It panned out ok  Pretty good weekend all in all. Couple shots at camp
Sweet looks like a good time and those are some beauty fish Andrew
Crazy the amount of snow up there this year. Like driving in a tunnel on the highway. Where’s your camp up around Wawa? I’m 40km north of Wawa on kabenung
Hey Slayer. Never had our January thaw, No bottom to the snow and wicked slush. I was at a buddies camp near Anjigami
Get that sink of dirty fishes cleaned up,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,  Nice fishes
Oh trust me I know about the slush! I got buried back in feb up at camp real bad for a few hours. Slush is everywhere this year!
I had rooster tails behind the vector. Ordered a new  Ski Doo Expedition for next year. Needed a bit more track  Fishes got cleaned 10 minutes after the photo
Very good choice. Did you order it with the 900ace?
Nope, 600 efi Wanted to keep weight and price down. I won't be putting enough miles on it to need a 4 stroke My Vector has 30,000 km on it.
LOVE that area.  Thanks Dara for the report and photos. Will you be able to access your buddy's camp (anjigami) again easily by railway once the new Agawa Canyon Railway begins passenger service?
